WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.583 --> 00:00:14.666
<i>Black holes are considered to be
the hellmouths of the universe.</i>

2
00:00:15.375 --> 00:00:18.833
<i>Those who fall inside disappear.</i>

3
00:00:19.541 --> 00:00:20.541
<i>Forever.</i>

4
00:00:24.750 --> 00:00:26.375
<i>But whereto?</i>

5
00:00:27.833 --> 00:00:31.333
<i>What lies behind a black hole?</i>

6
00:00:31.416 --> 00:00:33.125
<i>WHERE (WHEN) IS MIKKEL?</i>

7
00:00:33.208 --> 00:00:37.125
<i>Along with things.
do space and time also vanish there?</i>

8
00:00:37.208 --> 00:00:40.208
<i>Or would space and time</i>

9
00:00:40.291 --> 00:00:44.041
<i>be tied together
and be part of an endless cycle?</i>

10
00:00:44.666 --> 00:00:48.083
<i>What if everything that came from the past</i>

11
00:00:48.791 --> 00:00:52.625
<i>were influenced by the future?</i>

12
00:00:53.791 --> 00:00:55.208
Tick-tock.

13
00:00:55.708 --> 00:00:57.250
Tick-tock.

14
00:00:57.833 --> 00:00:59.083
Tick-tock.

15
00:00:59.625 --> 00:01:00.833
Tick-tock.

16
00:01:01.583 --> 00:01:02.583
Tick-tock.

17
00:01:03.625 --> 00:01:04.916
Tick-tock.

18
00:02:35.541 --> 00:02:40.208
DOUBLE LIVES

19
00:02:48.416 --> 00:02:50.375
The sneaky little bitch.

20
00:02:50.458 --> 00:02:52.375
Elli! Where's my lipstick?

21
00:02:56.583 --> 00:02:58.000
- Good morning.
- Morning.

22
00:03:02.333 --> 00:03:05.125
I'm going to stop by the home
to see Dad before work.

23
00:03:05.208 --> 00:03:06.208
Okay.

24
00:03:06.541 --> 00:03:08.583
I'll take Elisabeth to school.

25
00:03:08.666 --> 00:03:10.416
I don't want her to go by herself.

26
00:03:12.708 --> 00:03:13.708
All right.

27
00:03:26.041 --> 00:03:31.166
WINDEN CAVES

28
00:03:33.625 --> 00:03:36.125
WHERE IS THE CROSSING?

29
00:03:51.541 --> 00:03:53.000
There you are. you stupid cow!

30
00:03:56.250 --> 00:03:58.333
Where's my red lipstick?

31
00:03:58.916 --> 00:04:01.583
I don't have your stupid lipstick.

32
00:04:01.666 --> 00:04:05.333
I'm only eight. I don't use lipstick.

33
00:04:05.416 --> 00:04:07.500
You may be able
to fool those two upstairs

34
00:04:07.583 --> 00:04:09.291
with your puppy-dog eyes

35
00:04:09.375 --> 00:04:11.625
and your pitiful deaf-and-dumb act.

36
00:04:11.708 --> 00:04:13.708
but I don't buy it.

37
00:04:21.625 --> 00:04:24.000
Have you packed your backpack?
I'll drive you.

38
00:04:24.666 --> 00:04:26.291
Shall I take you too?

39
00:04:26.375 --> 00:04:27.791
Am I a baby or what?

40
00:04:28.458 --> 00:04:30.125
Because of Mikkel?

41
00:04:30.625 --> 00:04:32.000
Yes. because of Mikkel.

42
00:04:32.458 --> 00:04:35.000
Do you know who stole him?

43
00:04:35.083 --> 00:04:37.041
I won't discuss police work with you.

44
00:04:38.416 --> 00:04:40.791
I don't like Mikkel.
He's a show-off and a jerk.

45
00:04:42.708 --> 00:04:45.041
I don't really care if he ever comes back.

46
00:04:53.875 --> 00:04:54.875
Hey!

47
00:04:56.125 --> 00:04:57.583
Where are you going?

48
00:04:58.083 --> 00:04:59.083
To school.

49
00:04:59.166 --> 00:05:01.291
You don't have to go if you don't want to.

50
00:05:01.375 --> 00:05:02.875
I can call them.

51
00:05:04.791 --> 00:05:06.041
I'm fine.

52
00:05:09.375 --> 00:05:10.708
Jonas?

53
00:05:14.791 --> 00:05:17.041
We could also do something nice together.

54
00:05:18.208 --> 00:05:19.625
Just the two of us.

55
00:05:20.041 --> 00:05:21.166
Mom.

56
00:05:23.333 --> 00:05:24.375
Okay.

57
00:05:33.583 --> 00:05:35.875
REST HOME WINDEN

58
00:05:42.333 --> 00:05:43.458
Dad?

59
00:05:46.625 --> 00:05:48.416
You can't keep walking off.

60
00:05:49.291 --> 00:05:50.833
I have to tell him.

61
00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:53.625
Tell who what?

62
00:05:56.500 --> 00:05:58.125
I have to tell him.

63
00:05:59.208 --> 00:06:00.875
It has to stop.

64
00:06:03.541 --> 00:06:05.041
It has to stop.

65
00:06:05.125 --> 00:06:06.416
It has to...

66
00:06:09.291 --> 00:06:10.791
What has to stop?

67
00:06:10.875 --> 00:06:12.875
Tick-tock.

68
00:06:37.291 --> 00:06:38.833
Don't be sad.

69
00:06:40.625 --> 00:06:43.333
<i>Weeks ago. in the small town of Winden.</i>

70
00:06:43.416 --> 00:06:46.208
<i>a 15-year-old boy disappeared
under mysterious circumstances.</i>

71
00:06:46.291 --> 00:06:47.583
<i>MISSING</i>

72
00:06:47.708 --> 00:06:50.875
<i>Residents are now alarmed
after a second child has gone missing.</i>

73
00:06:51.000 --> 00:06:54.541
<i>11-year-old Mikkel
has been missing for two days.</i>

74
00:06:54.625 --> 00:06:57.666
<i>Please report any relevant information
to the Winden police.</i>

75
00:07:00.375 --> 00:07:03.500
<i>There have been repeated blackouts
in recent months</i>

76
00:07:04.375 --> 00:07:06.458
<i>Security and public facilities</i>

77
00:07:06.541 --> 00:07:09.000
<i>have not yet been...</i>

78
00:07:09.458 --> 00:07:12.125
<i>However.
power grid operators are promising</i>

79
00:07:12.208 --> 00:07:17.291
<i>to find the cause of the cuts and ask
the public to report further incidents.</i>

80
00:07:18.375 --> 00:07:20.166
CAUTION!
WILDLIFE OBSERVATION CAMERA

81
00:07:44.833 --> 00:07:46.750
Did you just steal something?

82
00:07:47.750 --> 00:07:51.041
I confiscated something.
there's a big difference.

83
00:07:51.583 --> 00:07:54.916
Whatever you call it.
it's still the same thing.

84
00:08:54.250 --> 00:08:56.000
I'll pick you up afterwards.

85
00:08:56.083 --> 00:08:58.625
I want you to wait for me. okay?

86
00:09:01.250 --> 00:09:02.791
What did I just say?

87
00:09:02.875 --> 00:09:04.458
That you'll pick me up.

88
00:09:07.666 --> 00:09:08.666
Who's he?

89
00:09:08.750 --> 00:09:10.750
Yasin. We're dating.

90
00:09:11.458 --> 00:09:13.041
You're doing what?

91
00:09:13.125 --> 00:09:15.541
Yasin is my boyfriend.

92
00:09:15.625 --> 00:09:17.291
That's how you say it nowadays.

93
00:09:18.625 --> 00:09:19.958
Well then...

94
00:09:40.708 --> 00:09:42.500
A web of symbols and references

95
00:09:42.750 --> 00:09:44.291
runs through the novel.

96
00:09:44.375 --> 00:09:48.708
The "sycamores by the sea" are an example
of this plethora of symbolism.

97
00:09:48.791 --> 00:09:52.458
A special form of repetition
in Goethe's work is what we call doubling.

98
00:09:52.541 --> 00:09:55.333
The characters
consciously and unconsciously...

99
00:10:04.666 --> 00:10:06.333
Magnus. this isn't your class.

100
00:10:07.875 --> 00:10:08.958
Won't you continue?

101
00:10:10.375 --> 00:10:11.375
Where was I...?

102
00:10:11.791 --> 00:10:14.708
Symmetry is a special kind of doubling.

103
00:10:15.166 --> 00:10:17.875
The repetition is mirrored
along a central axis.

104
00:10:18.166 --> 00:10:21.083
So. the repetition begins
at an imaginary center point

105
00:10:21.166 --> 00:10:24.375
and branches off
in two opposing directions.

106
00:10:24.958 --> 00:10:29.416
There are several encrypted references
to later events in the novel.

107
00:10:29.500 --> 00:10:31.500
Ottilie's starvation. for example.

108
00:10:31.583 --> 00:10:34.083
is referenced
in the third chapter of part one.

109
00:10:34.166 --> 00:10:37.416
as her "excessive abstemiousness
in eating and drinking."

110
00:10:37.500 --> 00:10:40.041
This reference is again repeated later.

111
00:10:40.666 --> 00:10:42.041
I have to go to the bathroom.

112
00:10:42.541 --> 00:10:44.166
Yes. Sure.

113
00:11:01.500 --> 00:11:04.000
I'm no ornithologist. but...

114
00:11:04.083 --> 00:11:06.083
these white speckles on the feathers

115
00:11:06.166 --> 00:11:07.916
are not typical of this species.

116
00:11:09.166 --> 00:11:11.875
Let's have a look at what killed you.

117
00:11:14.250 --> 00:11:15.875
Any news on the boy?

118
00:11:16.583 --> 00:11:19.333
Mikkel?
Disappeared off the face of the earth.

119
00:11:19.416 --> 00:11:21.708
No. not Mikkel. The dead boy.

120
00:11:21.791 --> 00:11:22.958
Oh. yes.

121
00:11:24.083 --> 00:11:25.208
No.

122
00:11:25.291 --> 00:11:28.916
We ran everything through
the missing persons database. No match.

123
00:11:32.500 --> 00:11:34.000
Everything okay with you?

124
00:11:38.291 --> 00:11:39.375
Yeah...

125
00:11:41.666 --> 00:11:42.666
No.

126
00:11:43.416 --> 00:11:45.791
I've seen spots like that
on feathers before.

127
00:11:46.666 --> 00:11:48.041
Thirty-three years ago.

128
00:11:50.458 --> 00:11:52.291
As if all this has happened before.

129
00:11:54.333 --> 00:11:55.333
The children.

130
00:11:56.500 --> 00:11:57.708
the birds...

131
00:12:00.250 --> 00:12:02.041
Somehow it's all connected.

132
00:12:02.125 --> 00:12:03.708
I just don't know how.

133
00:13:06.125 --> 00:13:09.375
Where have you been?
The phones have been ringing all morning.

134
00:13:09.458 --> 00:13:11.750
Someone must've said something
about the dead boy.

135
00:13:11.833 --> 00:13:13.125
What am I supposed to say?

136
00:13:13.208 --> 00:13:15.916
- Is Ulrich here?
- No. why?

137
00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:18.833
Go through
the missing persons database again.

138
00:13:18.916 --> 00:13:21.250
Include older reports this time.

139
00:13:21.708 --> 00:13:25.250
He may have disappeared a long time ago.
Check the last 15 years. okay?

140
00:13:25.791 --> 00:13:27.083
Right. okay.

141
00:13:27.166 --> 00:13:29.375
- Anything else?
- No. Actually. there is.

142
00:13:29.458 --> 00:13:30.833
The red soil...

143
00:13:30.916 --> 00:13:33.916
We can't find any.
Not anywhere close to where he was found.

144
00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:35.875
It must've come from the crime scene.

145
00:13:35.958 --> 00:13:37.875
Get Jankowski to look into it.

146
00:13:39.708 --> 00:13:41.833
And what do we say about the dead boy?

147
00:13:59.625 --> 00:14:00.750
What time is it?

148
00:14:01.541 --> 00:14:03.041
Just past ten.

149
00:14:09.708 --> 00:14:11.250
Charlotte called.

150
00:14:11.958 --> 00:14:15.125
She still doesn't have
a search warrant for the power plant.

151
00:14:17.291 --> 00:14:20.208
It's been nearly 36 hours. Ulrich.

152
00:14:47.708 --> 00:14:48.708
MISSING

153
00:14:50.916 --> 00:14:52.583
TIME OF DISAPPEARANCE 9:30 - 10:30 PM

154
00:15:28.916 --> 00:15:31.875
Should I continue with the tire tracks?
Seeing as Ulrich isn't in yet.

155
00:15:33.250 --> 00:15:34.333
Tire tracks?

156
00:15:37.375 --> 00:15:40.250
The treads we found on the road
the day Erik disappeared.

157
00:15:40.333 --> 00:15:41.833
No. I'll do that myself.

158
00:15:42.666 --> 00:15:44.791
- I can take it off your hands...
- I'll do it!

159
00:15:45.750 --> 00:15:46.750
Okay.

160
00:15:51.416 --> 00:15:53.958
- What's...
- A screenshot from a wildlife camera.

161
00:15:54.041 --> 00:15:56.166
I thought it might give us something.

162
00:15:58.125 --> 00:15:59.791
Are you done with the database?

163
00:16:00.708 --> 00:16:01.708
No.

164
00:16:01.791 --> 00:16:04.458
Then why are you asking me
about tire tracks?

165
00:16:06.041 --> 00:16:07.208
Fine.

166
00:17:05.458 --> 00:17:06.541
Charlotte?

167
00:17:07.458 --> 00:17:08.541
Is everything okay?

168
00:17:08.875 --> 00:17:13.125
I missed your call
on the evening Mikkel disappeared.

169
00:17:13.208 --> 00:17:15.125
I never asked why you called.

170
00:17:15.583 --> 00:17:17.083
Why did you call?

171
00:17:17.166 --> 00:17:18.250
I...

172
00:17:19.166 --> 00:17:20.500
I don't know. I...

173
00:17:21.333 --> 00:17:24.250
I think I was just calling
to say I'd be home late.

174
00:17:25.083 --> 00:17:26.583
Nothing special.

175
00:17:27.208 --> 00:17:29.625
You were at the office
all day on Monday?

176
00:17:30.250 --> 00:17:31.375
Yes... Yeah.

177
00:17:32.625 --> 00:17:34.291
I was writing reports

178
00:17:34.375 --> 00:17:37.041
until around ten in the evening.

179
00:17:37.125 --> 00:17:37.958
Why do you ask?

180
00:17:38.041 --> 00:17:39.666
TIME OF DISAPPEARANCE 9:30 - 10:30 PM

181
00:17:40.625 --> 00:17:41.875
No reason.

182
00:17:42.416 --> 00:17:44.833
I had something mailed to the office.

183
00:17:44.916 --> 00:17:47.958
and I'd forgotten about it.
I was just wondering if it arrived.

184
00:17:49.000 --> 00:17:50.666
We haven't received anything.

185
00:17:52.541 --> 00:17:53.541
Okay.

186
00:17:55.583 --> 00:17:56.583
Okay.

187
00:19:55.833 --> 00:19:57.666
I'm allowed to be parked here.

188
00:19:58.916 --> 00:20:01.625
I want to know
if Peter Doppler was one of your clients.

189
00:20:02.875 --> 00:20:04.166
Last Monday.

190
00:20:04.875 --> 00:20:06.583
Can I see your badge again?

191
00:20:13.416 --> 00:20:14.875
Charlotte Doppler.

192
00:20:17.833 --> 00:20:20.291
Is it a private or professional question?

193
00:20:22.083 --> 00:20:23.875
Does it make any difference?

194
00:20:26.375 --> 00:20:28.416
Was he here on Monday?

195
00:20:37.708 --> 00:20:38.708
Not necessary.

196
00:20:39.583 --> 00:20:41.541
I never forget a dick.

197
00:20:42.583 --> 00:20:45.291
Peter's is slightly crooked.
like a dill pickle.

198
00:20:45.875 --> 00:20:47.291
Feels weird in the mouth.

199
00:20:47.375 --> 00:20:50.500
- You probably know that already.
- Was he here on Monday or not?

200
00:20:57.916 --> 00:21:00.250
No. he hasn't been back in over a year.

201
00:21:02.291 --> 00:21:04.708
He must get what he needs
somewhere else now.

202
00:21:04.791 --> 00:21:05.791
Thanks.

203
00:22:06.750 --> 00:22:07.750
Fuck.

204
00:22:13.750 --> 00:22:15.500
<i>The beginning is the end.</i>

205
00:22:15.583 --> 00:22:17.708
<i>- and the end is the beginning.</i>
- Shit.

206
00:22:20.500 --> 00:22:22.500
The beginning is the end.

207
00:22:23.458 --> 00:22:25.416
and the end is the beginning.

208
00:22:27.500 --> 00:22:29.333
The beginning is the end...

209
00:22:29.875 --> 00:22:31.750
I left my kids at home today.

210
00:22:32.416 --> 00:22:33.500
My mom's there.

211
00:22:34.541 --> 00:22:35.708
She's looking after them.

212
00:22:36.333 --> 00:22:38.958
Supposedly they found
a body in the forest.

213
00:22:39.666 --> 00:22:40.666
You see...

214
00:22:40.750 --> 00:22:44.375
I have this pathologist friend. he said...

215
00:22:44.458 --> 00:22:46.416
it's terribly mutilated.

216
00:25:25.958 --> 00:25:27.791
- Yup?
<i>- Guess what?</i>

217
00:25:27.875 --> 00:25:30.166
- The bird has the same thing.
<i>- Has what?</i>

218
00:25:30.666 --> 00:25:33.166
Burst eardrums on both sides.

219
00:25:33.250 --> 00:25:35.500
- And that's how it died?
<i>- No.</i>

220
00:25:35.583 --> 00:25:39.583
It probably died from losing its bearings
and crashing into the ground.

221
00:25:39.666 --> 00:25:40.791
Cracked skull.

222
00:25:40.875 --> 00:25:45.166
It happens often. Electromagnetic fields
interfere with their sensory systems.

223
00:25:45.250 --> 00:25:46.875
- High voltage power lines?
<i>- No.</i>

224
00:25:46.958 --> 00:25:49.375
We're talking voltages
in the radio wave spectrum.

225
00:25:49.458 --> 00:25:50.708
Electrical appliances.

226
00:25:50.791 --> 00:25:53.750
- And the white spots in the feathers?
<i>- The white spots...</i>

227
00:25:53.833 --> 00:25:57.041
They started appearing after Chernobyl.
It's a kind of mutation.

228
00:25:57.125 --> 00:25:58.833
Radiation contamination?

229
00:25:58.916 --> 00:26:01.250
I checked.
but the radiation levels are normal.

230
00:26:02.125 --> 00:26:04.333
- Interesting.
<i>- It sure is.</i>

231
00:26:04.958 --> 00:26:06.791
<i>- Anything else?</i>
- Nope.

232
00:26:11.958 --> 00:26:15.666
And did you know the girl snails
bite the willies off the boy snails?

233
00:26:15.750 --> 00:26:17.875
You definitely made that one up.

234
00:26:18.791 --> 00:26:22.541
I didn't. Then the boys
keep crawling on as girls. No joke.

235
00:26:24.375 --> 00:26:25.851
- Where did you come up with that?
- Hey!

236
00:26:25.875 --> 00:26:27.875
- There you are. Yasin.
- Television.

237
00:26:28.250 --> 00:26:29.625
Let's go. Grandma's waiting.

238
00:26:36.416 --> 00:26:38.958
Should I give you a ride home?

239
00:26:39.833 --> 00:26:41.333
My mom's picking me up.

240
00:26:41.416 --> 00:26:43.333
I'll drive you home.

241
00:26:43.708 --> 00:26:45.083
It's no problem.

242
00:26:45.166 --> 00:26:48.791
My mom will be here any moment now.

243
00:26:48.875 --> 00:26:50.833
She's the Chief of Police.

244
00:26:51.250 --> 00:26:52.416
Okay.

245
00:26:54.416 --> 00:26:55.416
Come on.

246
00:28:44.458 --> 00:28:45.458
Yes?

247
00:28:46.958 --> 00:28:48.375
He did what?

248
00:29:02.458 --> 00:29:04.250
What the fuck?

249
00:29:07.208 --> 00:29:08.375
What's this?

250
00:29:08.916 --> 00:29:11.375
Money. you idiot. My money.

251
00:29:12.000 --> 00:29:13.750
Why do you have so much money?

252
00:29:14.250 --> 00:29:15.916
Are you dealing drugs?

253
00:29:16.000 --> 00:29:17.625
Is that why you were at the caves?

254
00:29:17.708 --> 00:29:20.083
How I earn my money
is none of your damn business.

255
00:29:21.458 --> 00:29:23.083
What are you going to do with it?

256
00:29:23.875 --> 00:29:27.750
What am I going to do with it?
I'm getting out of this phoney shithole.

257
00:29:28.333 --> 00:29:31.375
Behind everyone's friendly smile
there's nothing but lies.

258
00:29:32.000 --> 00:29:33.375
You're no different.

259
00:29:34.208 --> 00:29:37.041
You pretend to be the straight-A student.
but that's not you.

260
00:29:38.041 --> 00:29:41.291
- Maybe you should start telling the truth.
- You want the truth?

261
00:29:41.375 --> 00:29:42.375
Fine.

262
00:29:43.375 --> 00:29:46.083
My parents have slept
in different beds for over a year.

263
00:29:46.458 --> 00:29:49.583
My mom found out
that Dad's actually into dicks.

264
00:29:50.125 --> 00:29:52.541
Their marriage is over.
but no one will say it.

265
00:29:53.541 --> 00:29:56.708
Instead. this big fat secret
is always with us at the table.

266
00:29:56.791 --> 00:30:00.333
It eats our bread rolls.
the butter and the homemade jam.

267
00:30:00.750 --> 00:30:04.875
It gets fatter and fatter.
until there's no space left in the room.

268
00:30:05.875 --> 00:30:07.166
Until you can't breathe.

269
00:30:56.750 --> 00:30:58.833
- Did you forget something?
<i>- No.</i>

270
00:30:59.958 --> 00:31:02.833
You have to pick up Elisabeth from school.
I can't make it.

271
00:31:04.250 --> 00:31:07.166
I have a patient.
I have to go to the office.

272
00:31:07.708 --> 00:31:09.583
Just pick her up. okay?

273
00:31:09.666 --> 00:31:11.250
She can wait at your office.

274
00:31:11.625 --> 00:31:13.416
I have to go to the power plant.

275
00:31:14.041 --> 00:31:15.333
Okay. I'll...

276
00:31:17.041 --> 00:31:18.583
I'll pick her up.

277
00:31:18.666 --> 00:31:19.833
Thank you.

278
00:31:19.916 --> 00:31:21.083
Was that it?

279
00:31:21.166 --> 00:31:22.208
Wait.

280
00:31:22.791 --> 00:31:25.000
You made me a promise a year ago.

281
00:31:27.000 --> 00:31:29.833
If there's anything at all
you want to tell me...

282
00:31:36.083 --> 00:31:38.875
Hey. I really have to get going.
or else I'll be late.

283
00:32:30.833 --> 00:32:31.875
Tick-tock.

284
00:33:29.875 --> 00:33:30.875
Excuse me.

285
00:33:31.708 --> 00:33:33.833
I'm here to pick up Elisabeth.

286
00:33:34.625 --> 00:33:37.041
I thought she had already been picked up.

287
00:33:37.125 --> 00:33:38.125
What?

288
00:33:38.291 --> 00:33:41.000
Mrs. Clemens is sick.
School finished at two today.

289
00:33:41.541 --> 00:33:43.291
Didn't Elisabeth tell you?

290
00:33:44.583 --> 00:33:46.416
It was written in her homework book.

291
00:33:57.208 --> 00:34:01.333
Security found him on our grounds.
close to the caves.

292
00:34:01.791 --> 00:34:03.708
He must've climbed over the fence.

293
00:34:15.500 --> 00:34:17.791
He hasn't been very cooperative.

294
00:34:31.333 --> 00:34:33.833
You're lucky
Aleksander isn't pressing charges.

295
00:34:35.958 --> 00:34:39.250
Everyone understands your situation.
Everyone.

296
00:34:39.791 --> 00:34:41.541
But climbing over the fence?

297
00:34:42.458 --> 00:34:44.458
Understanding is nice. thank you.

298
00:34:45.625 --> 00:34:47.250
But it's not enough.

299
00:34:50.041 --> 00:34:51.875
My child is gone. okay?

300
00:34:51.958 --> 00:34:54.000
This isn't just some file on your desk.

301
00:34:54.083 --> 00:34:55.583
It's my child.

302
00:34:57.458 --> 00:34:58.708
Why Mikkel?

303
00:34:58.791 --> 00:35:01.250
I keep asking myself that.
Why him? Why my son?

304
00:35:01.333 --> 00:35:03.250
Why not his son?

305
00:35:03.333 --> 00:35:04.875
Why not his?

306
00:35:06.458 --> 00:35:08.041
I'm being punished.

307
00:35:09.250 --> 00:35:13.375
And all I get is fucking sympathy.
Well. you can take that and shove it.

308
00:35:13.458 --> 00:35:15.000
Where's the search warrant?

309
00:35:15.083 --> 00:35:17.041
Why is no one doing anything?

310
00:35:17.708 --> 00:35:20.625
Should I tell you why?
Because it's not his kid.

311
00:35:21.916 --> 00:35:23.875
And because it's not your kid.

312
00:35:26.250 --> 00:35:27.875
Stop here. I want to get out.

313
00:35:30.000 --> 00:35:31.125
Stop the car!

314
00:35:52.541 --> 00:35:54.791
- Yes?
- Elisabeth wasn't there.

315
00:35:55.375 --> 00:35:57.000
What do you mean not there?

316
00:35:57.083 --> 00:35:59.083
She wasn't at school.

317
00:35:59.166 --> 00:36:01.041
Mrs. Clemens is sick.

318
00:36:01.125 --> 00:36:03.125
She wasn't waiting there.

319
00:36:03.208 --> 00:36:06.708
I've been up and down the forest road
twice already. but she's not here.

320
00:36:07.166 --> 00:36:10.125
Maybe someone from school took her home?
Maybe Yasin?

321
00:36:10.208 --> 00:36:11.625
Go back home.

322
00:36:11.708 --> 00:36:14.541
Maybe she went a different way.
Call everyone in her class.

323
00:36:15.000 --> 00:36:16.666
I'll be there in 15 minutes.

324
00:37:26.166 --> 00:37:27.500
Yes. all right.

325
00:37:29.541 --> 00:37:30.708
Thank you.

326
00:37:35.541 --> 00:37:37.541
I've called everyone on the list.

327
00:37:38.125 --> 00:37:39.333
Nothing.

328
00:40:00.125 --> 00:40:01.750
I have to tell him.

329
00:40:02.416 --> 00:40:03.958
He has to stop.

330
00:40:33.458 --> 00:40:34.541
I lost my hat.

331
00:40:35.458 --> 00:40:36.875
Where were you?

332
00:40:37.666 --> 00:40:40.583
You didn't pick me up. so I walked.

333
00:40:41.250 --> 00:40:44.208
And that took you this long?

334
00:40:45.583 --> 00:40:47.125
I met someone.

335
00:40:53.416 --> 00:40:55.458
He gave me this.

336
00:40:56.000 --> 00:40:57.083
Who did?

337
00:40:57.166 --> 00:40:59.125
Ouch! You're hurting me.

338
00:40:59.208 --> 00:41:02.166
I want to know who gave this to you.

339
00:41:02.250 --> 00:41:03.291
Noah.

340
00:41:04.291 --> 00:41:06.500
Who is Noah?

341
00:41:07.083 --> 00:41:10.416
He said it used to belong to you.

342
00:41:15.875 --> 00:41:17.541
- You are all cold...
- <i>Elli?</i>

343
00:41:18.791 --> 00:41:19.875
Elli. is that you?

344
00:41:25.916 --> 00:41:27.666
I was so worried about you.

345
00:41:30.708 --> 00:41:32.208
Where were you?

346
00:41:41.166 --> 00:41:42.625
Hands off my stuff!

347
00:41:49.291 --> 00:41:50.291
Hello?

348
00:41:50.958 --> 00:41:51.958
Yes.

349
00:41:52.875 --> 00:41:53.875
No. she's here now.

350
00:41:53.958 --> 00:41:55.250
Just now.

351
00:41:56.541 --> 00:41:57.541
What?

352
00:41:59.833 --> 00:42:01.458
Yes. I'll be right there.

353
00:42:03.541 --> 00:42:07.041
Wöller found Helge in the woods.

354
00:42:10.208 --> 00:42:13.291
FOR CHARLOTTE

355
00:42:20.916 --> 00:42:25.083
We're searching for Ariadne's thread.

356
00:42:25.833 --> 00:42:29.500
the one meant
to guide us along the right path.

357
00:42:31.125 --> 00:42:34.625
A beacon in the darkness.

358
00:42:36.250 --> 00:42:39.750
We'd love to know our fate.

359
00:42:40.833 --> 00:42:42.916
Where we're headed.

360
00:42:45.375 --> 00:42:50.708
But the truth is that there is
but one path through all times.

361
00:42:52.708 --> 00:42:56.416
Predetermined by the beginning

362
00:42:56.500 --> 00:42:58.541
and by the end.

363
00:42:59.875 --> 00:43:02.333
Which is also the beginning.

364
00:43:14.458 --> 00:43:15.583
He has to stop.

365
00:43:17.500 --> 00:43:18.916
Who has to stop?

366
00:43:19.000 --> 00:43:20.708
I have to stop him.

367
00:43:21.333 --> 00:43:22.333
Stop whom?

368
00:43:25.208 --> 00:43:26.208
Noah.

369
00:43:40.541 --> 00:43:43.333
I'm not a baby anymore.

370
00:43:43.416 --> 00:43:47.500
I can go to school on my own!

371
00:44:09.541 --> 00:44:10.958
You must be Yasin.

372
00:44:12.500 --> 00:44:13.750
Noah sent me.
